1
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:09,833
[AIKA]
Hey, Kimito!

2
00:00:09,916 --> 00:00:11,791
How do Commoners
get their fortunes told?

3
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:13,083
Our phones.

4
00:00:13,166 --> 00:00:16,041
We use fortune telling apps
and websites, too.

5
00:00:16,125 --> 00:00:18,083
You're totally blowing
my mind right now!

6
00:00:18,166 --> 00:00:19,583
Okay, show me!

7
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:21,125
Yeah. Sure.

8
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:24,000
[MOON (ERI)]
You don't need the cosmos.

9
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:25,333
You've got me!

10
00:00:25,416 --> 00:00:27,208
Hey, that sounds
like your friend.

11
00:00:27,291 --> 00:00:29,583
Yup. This was
one of her first jobs.

12
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:31,750
Cool.

13
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,000
Get ready, because
here comes your fortune!

14
00:00:34,083 --> 00:00:35,166
Sweet Aika...

15
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:36,625
The walls around your
brain are too thin

16
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:39,291
to keep in your thoughts!
That's why you're so blunt!

17
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:40,375
You blurt out your thoughts

18
00:00:40,458 --> 00:00:42,500
'cause there's nothing
to stop them!

19
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:44,791
It's the reason you
keep people at arm's length!

20
00:00:44,875 --> 00:00:48,208
Wow! That's so me!
This is incredible!

21
00:00:48,291 --> 00:00:49,583
All I did was
put in my birthday,

22
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:51,750
and she summed up my
personality perfectly!

23
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:53,583
All in the blink of an eye!

24
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:56,541
This is the greatest
invention of all time!

25
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:59,833
Look. It has your lucky
color written down as well.

26
00:00:59,916 --> 00:01:01,083
Let me see!

27
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:04,125
Well?

28
00:01:04,208 --> 00:01:05,250
What is that?

29
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:07,500
The app says green
is my lucky color!

30
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:10,583
So if I cover myself with it,
then, for the rest of my life,

31
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:12,166
I'll always have good luck!

32
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:13,250
Brilliant plan.

33
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,041
But you missed a spot.
Your face.

34
00:01:15,125 --> 00:01:16,291
[AIKA]
Good call.

35
00:01:16,375 --> 00:01:18,541
If I want this to work,
I have to really commit.

36
00:01:18,625 --> 00:01:20,833
[AIKA] Hey, wait.
What about my palms?

37
00:01:20,916 --> 00:01:22,666
Shouldn't I do something
to green them up a bit?

38
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:23,625
Do it, Aika.

39
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,125
Go green all the way!

40
00:01:30,375 --> 00:01:32,916
[AIKA] How do I look?
Great, or super great?

41
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,125
[KIMITO]
Mega great!

42
00:01:34,208 --> 00:01:35,666
And while you're holding
those edamame beans,

43
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:38,333
you should dance around and
shout for all the world to hear.

44
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:39,583
"Beans, beans!"

45
00:01:39,666 --> 00:01:40,708
[AIKA]
Wait, why?

46
00:01:40,791 --> 00:01:42,333
It's a Commoner
dance we always do

47
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:44,041
the day before spring starts.

48
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:45,416
It'll bring you good luck.

49
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,708
[AIKA]
For real?

50
00:01:46,791 --> 00:01:49,041
My dad would scatter
soybeans on Spring's Eve.

51
00:01:49,125 --> 00:01:50,416
Do Commoners do that, too?

52
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:52,500
Yeah. But we also do the dance,

53
00:01:52,583 --> 00:01:53,916
and even though
it's not Spring's Eve,

54
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,208
I think you should try it.

55
00:01:55,291 --> 00:01:56,375
You've gone this far.

56
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:58,375
Might as well take it
to the next level.

57
00:01:58,458 --> 00:01:59,750
Make me proud.

58
00:01:59,833 --> 00:02:01,750
[AIKA] But shouldn't I
be using soybeans for this?

59
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:04,250
[KIMITO] Edamame beans
are baby soybeans.

60
00:02:04,333 --> 00:02:05,500
[AIKA]
I didn't know that!

61
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:07,458
Break it down, Aika. Let loose!

62
00:02:07,541 --> 00:02:09,833
Bust a move and get
yourself some good luck!

63
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:13,375
[AIKA]
Beans, beans! Beans, beans!

64
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:14,875
Beans, beans! Beans, beans!

65
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:16,333
[KIMITO]
Attaway, Aika!

66
00:02:16,416 --> 00:02:17,458
[AIKA]
Beans, beans!

67
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:19,041
[KIMITO]
Do your thing!

68
00:02:19,125 --> 00:02:20,125
[AIKA]
Yeah!

69
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:21,166
[KIMITO]
Take it from the top!

70
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,000
[AIKA]
Right! Beans, beans!

71
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:26,083
Beans, beans! Beans, beans!

72
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:27,125
Yeah!

73
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:31,208
[REIKO]
This is certainly... peculiar.

74
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,541
Get ready, because
here comes your fortune!

75
00:04:05,625 --> 00:04:06,625
Kind Reiko...

76
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:08,250
You live for the
daily contact you have

77
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:10,500
with the many friends
who surround you.

78
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:13,958
Because of your excellent powers
of observation and analysis,

79
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:16,791
you will find success
in doing management work.

80
00:04:16,875 --> 00:04:19,500
You are relentless in
your pursuit of romance.

81
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:20,750
Oh my!

82
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:23,125
For a digitized gypsy,
she's quite accurate!

83
00:04:23,208 --> 00:04:25,958
Totes! It's like she
can see inside our souls!

84
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:26,958
That it is.

85
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:28,458
Why don't we let
Hakua try it next?

86
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,250
Darling Hakua...

87
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:33,125
You're like a
walking contradiction.

88
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:34,750
So hard to pin down.

89
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:36,708
Depending on the day,
you're either fully invested

90
00:04:36,791 --> 00:04:38,250
or fiercely apathetic.

91
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:41,125
You have a scholar's mind,
and an artist's temperament.

92
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:42,291
She's got you there!

93
00:04:42,375 --> 00:04:44,500
Commoner fortune
telling is beyond belief!

94
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:46,291
What a lovely civilization!

95
00:04:46,375 --> 00:04:47,500
[KIMITO chuckles]

96
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:49,458
It's surprising how
accurate this thing is.

97
00:04:49,541 --> 00:04:51,750
I mean, it pretty much
described you perfectly.

98
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,750
[KAREN]
So pointless!

99
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:56,333
What could some
fortune telling app

100
00:04:56,416 --> 00:04:57,708
possibly know about me?

101
00:04:57,791 --> 00:04:59,666
I simply will not allow
myself to be caught up

102
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:01,875
in such childish,
inane frivolities!

103
00:05:01,958 --> 00:05:03,041
Well, if that's really true,

104
00:05:03,125 --> 00:05:04,458
then you won't mind
if I go next.

105
00:05:04,541 --> 00:05:05,708
You're an idiot!

106
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:08,416
You obviously want to try it.

107
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,791
[KAREN] Only to see
what it knows of my skill!

108
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:11,791
Go ahead.

109
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:13,708
If this machine
is truly accurate,

110
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:15,666
then it will laud
my noble way of life,

111
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:18,166
and my unparalleled
ability to wield a sword

112
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:19,416
in the throes of combat.

113
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:20,750
Pretty sure you're wrong there.

114
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,458
[phone chiming]

115
00:05:22,541 --> 00:05:25,083
Mighty Karen...
You are extremely lonely.

116
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:27,666
And your melancholy makes you
act in an aggressive way.

117
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:29,708
You're a scatterbrained
worrywart who lives your life

118
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:33,125
in a constant state of panic,
anxiety and distress.

119
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:35,250
When it comes to romance,
you are passive at best

120
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,125
and completely inept at worst.

121
00:05:37,208 --> 00:05:39,416
This must be some
kind of terrible mistake!

122
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:42,083
[KIMITO]
Really? Sounds dead on to me.

123
00:05:42,166 --> 00:05:43,708
[KAREN]
Let me see that!

124
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:45,333
I only got such
an absurd result

125
00:05:45,416 --> 00:05:46,916
because you were
the one holding it.

126
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,416
Let's see if things
aren't a little different

127
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,625
this time around!

128
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:54,583
[KAREN] Test your romantic
compatibility with friends?

129
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:04,125
As members of the Commoner Club,

130
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:05,833
it is our mandate
to explore this.

131
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:08,458
I, for one, firmly believe that
we should learn all we can

132
00:06:08,541 --> 00:06:09,708
from this app.

133
00:06:09,791 --> 00:06:10,416
As do I.

134
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,208
A valid point.

135
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:12,375
[HAKUA]
Yeah.

136
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:13,583
I'm glad you agree.

137
00:06:13,666 --> 00:06:14,958
Now then,
let's make full use of

138
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,458
this vaunted
fortune telling apparatus.

139
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:19,625
Sadly, it only
tells compatibility

140
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:21,041
between the opposite sexes.

141
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:22,791
Since Kimito is the only boy,

142
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:25,458
we'll need to have it evaluate
our compatibility with him.

143
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,500
Normally, more choices
would be ideal.

144
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:29,666
But as it stands,
he's our only option.

145
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,041
Yeah. Too bad.

146
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:32,291
We'll just have to make do.

147
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:34,958
Yes, painful though it may be.

148
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:37,708
[KIMITO] I've never seen them
agree like this before.

149
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:40,041
Well, I guess this is
today's club activity.

150
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:43,166
Should go fine, as long
as it's all in good fun.

151
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:44,708
Let's get started, then.

152
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:46,333
Care to go first, Kimito?

153
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:48,208
Sure. I'm glad to.

154
00:06:48,291 --> 00:06:49,833
But don't you think
everyone's acting weird?

155
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:51,041
[REIKO]
Weird?

156
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:53,041
Never mind. It's nothing.

157
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:55,625
Well, how about we
start things off with you?

158
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:56,583
Is something wrong?

159
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,125
[REIKO]
Oh, no!

160
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:00,541
That just wouldn't be fair.

161
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:01,416
[AIKA gasps]

162
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,208
Let's go alphabetically!

163
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:05,416
[AIKA, KIMITO]
So then... A for Aika.

164
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,000
[AIKA]
Sure, I guess.

165
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:09,083
What's this?

166
00:07:09,166 --> 00:07:10,291
What?

167
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:12,625
That's cool.
It gives us a numerical score.

168
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:14,083
[AIKA]
How many points did I get?

169
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:16,000
Uh... Well...

170
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:17,458
[KIMITO gasps]

171
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:19,166
[KIMITO]
Uh... Oh boy.

172
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:21,291
Spit it out!

173
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:22,333
[REIKO] Hurry up
and tell us the number!

174
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:23,416
[KAREN]
Quit stalling!

175
00:07:24,958 --> 00:07:26,250
Uh...

176
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,625
Hakua, did you mean to
punch me in the shin, or...?

177
00:07:27,708 --> 00:07:28,708
Yes.

178
00:07:28,791 --> 00:07:30,291
Okay. Right.

179
00:07:30,375 --> 00:07:33,208
Me and Aika's
compatibility score is--

180
00:07:33,291 --> 00:07:34,833
You got 80 points!

181
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:36,125
This may take you by surprise,

182
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:37,750
but the truth is
the two of you would make

183
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,458
quite an extraordinary couple!

184
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:41,166
A strong romance
is often built upon

185
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,416
the foundation of friendship,

186
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,083
and that is certainly
the case here!

187
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:49,375
[AIKA]
All right!

188
00:07:50,416 --> 00:07:51,958
[AIKA squealing]

189
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:55,291
[AIKA giggling, cheering]

190
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,375
So earlier, I got
excited 'cause I thought

191
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:02,375
my lucky green body suit
was paying off!

192
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:04,333
But then I realized luck's
got nothin' to do with it

193
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:06,166
'cause some things
are just meant to be!

194
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:08,500
And clearly that's
the case with me and Kimito.

195
00:08:08,583 --> 00:08:11,208
Not that I'm into him,
but hey, destiny's spoken.

196
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:12,541
[REIKO]
I'd like to go next, please.

197
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:14,458
And I realize that might
appear to be out of order.

198
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:16,875
But in all reality,
I should've been first anyway,

199
00:08:16,958 --> 00:08:19,291
considering my last name
starts with an A.

200
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:20,666
Uh huh.

201
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,458
Aww, isn't it sweet how
bad Reiko wants to go next?

202
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:24,625
Sure hope she gets
what she wants.

203
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:27,208
However, against a
score as high as mine,

204
00:08:27,291 --> 00:08:29,750
I don't think she has much
of a chance of winning out!

205
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:32,541
And just in case you all forgot,
my score was 80!

206
00:08:32,625 --> 00:08:33,958
Good luck, Reiko!

207
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:35,125
[AIKA laughs]

208
00:08:35,208 --> 00:08:36,333
Please tell me
our results, and quickly.

209
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:38,458
I'm dying to know!

210
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:40,750
90 points! That's amazing!

211
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:43,750
You two are perfectly suited
for the bonds of matrimony!

212
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:45,541
Together, your life
as a married couple

213
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:48,375
would be long, joyous
and incredibly fruitful.

214
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:57,000
Oh my! 90 points indeed!

215
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:59,625
And she says we're highly
suited for marriage as well!

216
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:02,041
This is the greatest day
of my entire life!

217
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:03,041
You're wrong! No!

218
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,333
This has to be a mistake!

219
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:06,125
Aww... Come now, Aika.

220
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:09,041
We should be glad that we both
received favorable results.

221
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:11,958
For my part, I am quite pleased
with my score of 90.

222
00:09:12,041 --> 00:09:14,125
And what was your
score again, Aika?

223
00:09:14,208 --> 00:09:16,291
I don't remember.
Wasn't it lower?

224
00:09:17,666 --> 00:09:19,791
How 'bout you, Hakua? Wanna try?

225
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:24,708
[KIMITO]
I didn't wanna leave her out,

226
00:09:24,791 --> 00:09:26,916
but this could definitely
get a little awkward.

227
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,666
Here goes.

228
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,125
50 points.

229
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:32,541
Kimito and Hakua, it seems
the chemistry between you

230
00:09:32,625 --> 00:09:33,833
is neither good nor bad.

231
00:09:33,916 --> 00:09:35,750
Because Hakua hardly ever speaks

232
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:37,291
and is not much
of a communicator,

233
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:39,333
you two will have
to work extremely hard

234
00:09:39,416 --> 00:09:41,458
even to understand one another.

235
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:43,416
[KIMITO] Not sure what
I was hopin' for with that.

236
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,500
All right,
time for damage control.

237
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:48,333
Oh well, it's just
a silly game, right?

238
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:49,750
Who wants some tea?

239
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:51,833
[KIMITO]
Hakua?

240
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,791
Okay, then.

241
00:09:55,875 --> 00:09:57,333
I know what always
makes me feel better

242
00:09:57,416 --> 00:09:58,458
when I'm feeling sad.

243
00:09:58,541 --> 00:09:59,625
Delicious goodies!

244
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:00,833
Awesome idea!

245
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:02,750
I'll go get 'em real quick!

246
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:04,083
[door opens, closes]

247
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:06,041
[KIMITO] Honestly,
I don't think she's that upset.

248
00:10:07,583 --> 00:10:09,375
Whelp, that leaves
the two of us.

249
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:13,208
I can't very well be the
only one who doesn't try it.

250
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:16,250
[KIMITO] Hey. If you don't
want to, it's no big deal.

251
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,458
But I can tell by the look
on your face, you secretly do.

252
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:23,750
[KAREN] You know nothing
about what I want, you fiend!

253
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:26,083
Yeah. Right.

254
